Package manifest for `ctx-cage`, the crate providing an offline `bwrap`-based sandbox for autonomous agent runs — a writable workspace, masked secrets, and a host-side API proxy as the only permitted egress path.

Defines two binaries and a library: `ctx-cage` (src/bin/ctx_cage.rs, the low-level cage launcher) and `ctx-run` (src/bin/ctx_run.rs, the one-command billed launcher wrapping it), plus the `ctx_cage` lib crate (src/lib.rs) that both binaries presumably share. Depends on `clap` for CLI parsing, `serde_json` for structured I/O (likely proxy/config messages), and `thiserror` for error types. Not published. Uses workspace-level lint settings rather than its own. No sandboxing logic lives in this file — actual `bwrap` invocation, namespace setup, and proxy behavior are in the referenced src/ files, not deducible from the manifest alone.